  "prompt": "Why is Modi not attending the Parliament after demonetization?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi has been actively participating in parliamentary sessions and fulfilling his duties as the head of government. It's possible that there might be some confusion regarding the timeline or specific events related to demonetization and parliamentary attendance. Here's some context to clarify:\n\n### **Demonetization in India**\n- **Date:** November 8, 2016\n- **Action:** The Modi-led government announced the demonetization of all \u20b9500 and \u20b91,000 banknotes.\n- **Purpose:** The primary goals were to combat black money, reduce counterfeit currency, and encourage a shift towards a digital economy.\n\n### **Post-Demonetization Parliamentary Attendance**\n- **Continued Participation:** After the demonetization event in 2016, Prime Minister Modi continued to attend parliamentary sessions regularly. There hasn't been any significant or credible report indicating that he ceased attending Parliament specifically due to the demonetization policy.\n  \n### **Possible Reasons for Misunderstanding**\n1. **Temporary Absences:** Like any head of government, Prime Minister Modi may occasionally be absent from parliamentary sessions due to international commitments, health reasons, or other official duties. Such absences are typically temporary and planned.\n   \n2. **Political Criticism:** Demonitization has been a topic of extensive debate and criticism. It's possible that discussions around its impacts might lead to misconceptions about the Prime Minister's engagement with Parliament.\n\n3. **Misinformation:** In the age of digital information, misinformation can sometimes spread rapidly. Ensure that the sources of such claims are credible.\n\n### **Current Status (As of October 2023)**\n- **Active Role:** Narendra Modi remains an active leader in Indian politics and continues to lead the government. He participates in legislative processes, addresses Parliament, and engages in policymaking.\n  \n- **Scheduled Sessions:** Parliamentary schedules can vary, and the Prime Minister's participation is aligned with these schedules unless overridden by exceptional circumstances.\n\n### **Recommendations**\n- **Verify Sources:** If you've come across recent information suggesting that Prime Minister Modi isn't attending Parliament post-demonetization, it's essential to verify this with reliable news outlets or official government statements.\n  \n- **Stay Updated:** For the most current information beyond October 2023, please refer to reputable news sources or the official [Prime Minister's Office (PMO) website](https://www.pmindia.gov.in/) for updates on his activities and parliamentary attendance.\n\nIf there's a specific incident or report you're referring to, please provide more details, and I can help clarify further based on the available information up to October 2023.",
